          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I use the device on other areas of my body?",
            "text": "<p>The NeuroMD Corrective Therapy Device can be used on other areas however, we do not recommend use on the front of the neck, across the chest, or on the head.<br/>The device will improve musculoskeletal health and function on the area it is applied. For example if you're having muscle spasms in your mid back you would apply the device in that area.<br/><br/>In order to obtain the best degree of pain relief with NeuroMD, we recommend the following pad placement guidelines:<br/><br/>1. Take note of exactly where your pain is located. Outline the most concise and tender area of the pain.<br/>2. The pad can be placed in one of three directions 1. vertical 2. horizontal 3. angulated.<br/>3. It is advisable not to place the pad directly over a joint such as the knee, elbow or ankle as its movement can alter the adherence of the pad.<br/>4. Increase intensity gradually as each body part will tolerate a different level of intensity<br/>Note: Pad placement as well as Intensity level tolerance varies from person to person. We recommend following our guidelines and do what feels best for you.</p>",
            "content": ""
